What is the standard layout style for Curv code?

The offside rule.
It should look like Lisp or Python, ignoring punctuation.
The goal is readability. The structure editor will take care of writability.

Mixfix:
  if ... then
    ...
  else if ... then
    ...
  else
    ...

  let
    A
  in do
    B
  in
    C

Lists and records
  [ A,
    B,
    C ]
or
  [A,
   B,
   C]

{x=1;
 y=2;
 z=3}
